</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 9:25
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='554000' id='t-554000'>Nowadays, the user is actually involved.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='557000' id='t-557000'>This is actually what's called, in the digital world, &quot;user-generated content.&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='560000' id='t-560000'>Although it's called agriculture in the world of food.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='562000' id='t-562000'>(Laughter)</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='563000' id='t-563000'>This is actually called a mash-up,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='565000' id='t-565000'>where you take content that someone else has produced</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='567000' id='t-567000'>and you do something new with it.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='569000' id='t-569000'>In the world of food we call it cooking.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='572000' id='t-572000'>This is food 2.0,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='574000' id='t-574000'>which is food you produce for the purpose of sharing it with other people.</span>
