<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='630000' id='t-630000'>at the University of Stanford, makes the point</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='632000' id='t-632000'>that actually the mobile phone is --</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='634000' id='t-634000'>He's invented the phrase, &quot;persuasive technologies.&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='636000' id='t-636000'>He believes the mobile phone, by being location-specific,</span>
